Synopsis
In 1930s Chicago, the people know hitman Michael O'Sullivan (Tom Hanks) 
as the Angel of Death, but he's also a devoted husband and father 
of two boys. When business and family collide, Sullivan will do anything 
to protect those he loves. Paul Newman stars as Sullivan's boss and Jude 
Law plays an assassin with a bent for photography. Directed by Sam Mendes 
('American Beauty'), this film is adapted from the graphic 
novel of the same title.
